          çSpecial seasonally afflicted Xmas demo supplement!

And this was a time of year just gone where presents were exchanged, 
family members visit, and occasionally, fight one another, too much 
food eaten. and the oh so inevitable cheap and cheerful quick Xmas demo 
releases follow..

 Paranoia X-Mass Demo..

Having a whole 24 hours to spare on this demo soon reaps rewards, 
firstly in the shape of a tasteful 'Millenium bug' joke where the use-
by dates on a carton of milk, a tin of cola ('Pupsi' - The cola drink 
for dogs?) and a typical 'entry-level PC of today are all displayed.. 
The PC's 'use-by' date is, of course, the 1st of January 2000!

Personally, I think it's unfair on the carton of milk to compare a PC 
with it, as every fool know that we're really looking at something like 
a  snowflake in July to accurately measure the life span of a PC 
against!

The second part of this little demo is a more routine Xmas scene, with 
a bit of a twist with a gift-wrapped razor blade, surely not being sent 
to Moondog? A greets text, and burbly YM-generated 'traditional' Xmas 
type music..

Oh, and close the door behind you, when you reset your computer..

 60% - 'Yule' be sorry for not getting this one! (doohh!)


 Mary Xmas from da Boosters..

Animated Xmas card type of thing, a bit like a 'Nun' production, but 
without access to fancy Dan state-of-the-art graphics hardware, sort of 
homely scribble, like the Senior Dads (whatever happened to them, now 
that was a Fake Crew with aspirations..)

Then all over..

 50% - Brandy Butter..


 SnowStorm / Reservoir Gods..

This effort is easily the most ambitious of the '98 crop of Xmas demos, 
that is to say, not very..

However, we are grateful even for small mercies. and clicking off with 
a smart Res Gods logo and a kicking MSG soundtrack which only slowly 
turns into something 'naughty and nice' along a more 'Xmassy' theme..

The main effect is showcased, a smooth 3-D 'snowfield' (as in 
starfield, but blobbier) with various effects going into the camera 
view, including such anti-social deviancy as end on end tumbling.. (Mr 
Pink also says that there are more snowflakes on an RGB monitor, over a 
VGA one!) At the same time, there is an extended greets, session 
scrolling away at the bottom of the screen.. So it is a plan to save 
money on sending out Xmas cards then!

There are various Xmas cards from MSG's table which paint themselves 
onscreen in an exhibitionist fashion.. These have been scanned in, 
including one I seem to remember sending myself..

Then it goes around again..

 72% - Play your Xmas cards right to get greeted here?
 

Anyone want to know my 1999 wish? No, not the call-girls and cold 
custard one, people aren't supposed to know about that, not with me 
going out with someone and all... Ahem!!

Please, more ambitious fake demos.. I'm not going to go all 'Moondog' 
on fake crews and slag them out of hand, but some of the recent efforts 
are just a tad on the short  side? There is only so much interest you 
can summon up for a single screen with an average joke..

Good luck for '99 though..

